{"id": 227794530, "title": "Letters, June 2: Oilers fans spellbound by coach Knoblauch", "text": "MAD GENIUS Have the Oilers finally found their new saviour? Heading into Game 6, just one win away from the Stanley Cup Final for the first time since 2006, it appears that Kris Knoblauch has the magical touch. Our coaching \u2018mad scientist\u2019 has made many bold and controversial lineup decisions that have, so far, led to on-ice success. Keep up the good work Kris, the fan base is currently spellbound! AL WILLEY (The way he pulled this team out of a tailspin and guided them to this point is nothing short of remarkable.) A BAD LOOK For the fourth time in six months, an Edmonton police officer has been disciplined for drinking and driving. Common sense says those who behave this way do not belong in law enforcement. We all make mistakes, but some are not forgivable. What does it take for EPS leadership to acknowledge this serious problem? There has been rising criticism of the lack of leadership within Edmonton Police. Their lack of acknowledgment tells us just how seriously they view their indiscretions.", "summary": "VOTE IN OUR DAILY POLL: Will you take in next weekend\u2019s Dragon Festival? MAD GENIUS Have the Oilers finally found their new saviour? Heading into Game 6, just one win away from the Stanley Cup Final for the first time since 2006, it appears that Kris Knoblauch has the magical touch. Our coaching \u2018mad scientist\u2019 [&#8230;]", "url": "https://edmontonsun.com/opinion/letters/letters-june-2-oilers-fans-spellbound-by-coach-knoblauch", "image": "https://smartcdn.gprod.postmedia.digital/edmontonsun/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/oilers-penguins-hockey.jpg?quality=100&strip=all", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-02 12:00:10", "author": "Barry Hanson,Edmonton Sun", "authors": ["Barry Hanson", "Edmonton Sun"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ca", "sentiment": -0.019}